==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Horde
<hw>Horde</hw> <pr>(h⟦omac⟧rd)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>horde</ets> (cf. G. <ets>horde</ets>), fr. Turk.
<ets>ord⟦umac⟧</ets>, <ets>ord⟦imac⟧</ets>, camp; of Tartar
origin.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A wandering troop or gang; especially, a
clan or tribe of a nomadic people migrating from place to place for the
sake of pasturage, plunder, etc.; a predatory multitude.</def>
<rj><au>Thomson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>Any large group of people or
animals, especially one wandering or moving about; <as>as, the movie
star was surrounded by a <ex>horde</ex> of screaming
fans</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hordeic</ent>⟦br⟧
